docs.lead_paragraph: DEAR SIR. As a faithful delegate from the free democracy of Boston, I had counted upon sharing the councils and encouragement of our State Convention at Fitchburg, this day; but the physician into whose hands I have fallen this week, admonishes me that I cannot make the necessary effort at this time without endangering the recovery of may health.

headline.main: PHILADELPHIA.; The State of the weather--Yellow Fever Accidents--Markets, &c.

docs.lead_paragraph: The rain is now falling rapidly and many of our streets are flooded with water. It is, however, a welcome visiter, and must be productive of much good. The heat, in the earlier part of the day, was quite oppressive.

docs.lead_paragraph: Their Majesties are still absent upon their incognito excursion. The enthusiasm, or starting, by which ever name you choose to call it, seems to continue. Jaunts at sea and little rides on the coast are found to benefit the Empress' health.

headline.main: THE YELLOW FEVER AT THE SOUTH.

docs.lead_paragraph: New-Orleans. The official report of interments in New-Orleans, for the week ending September 11, is as follows: Yellow fever, 399; other diseases, 131 : total, 530 On the 11th there were 68 deaths, of which 48 were of yellow fever; on the 12th, 55 deaths, of which 40 were of yellow fever.

docs.lead_paragraph: Hon. VICTORY BIRDSEYR.--The Syracuse Journal, in announcing the death of lion. VICTORY BIRDSEYE, of Onondaga County, which occurred on Friday last, adds the following: He had been in apparently good health and spirits, and retired to bed as usual, without suspicion of ailment; but, not appealing in the morning, one of the family proceeded to his room and found him a corpse.

headline.main: GREAT BRITAIN.; POLITICAL AND GENERAL NEWS. Personal and Theatrical Intelligence.

docs.lead_paragraph: Lord PALMERSTON is employing his temporary release from his arduous duties at the Home Office, in a provincial tour. The other day he laid the foundation-stone of a new "Athenaeum," at Melbourne, in Derbyshire, where he possesses estates. The proprietors of the new Institute were peculiarly fortunate in securing his lordship to open it.

byline.original: CORRESPONDENCE OF THE N. Y. DAILY TIMES

docs.lead_paragraph: The Board of Health report two yellow fever deaths during the past week in this city. The disease was brought here, it will be remembered, by the bark Mandarin, and still lingers about Southstreet wharf; and LATHAM'S lead-pipe factory, located there, has been closed in consequence of the dread entertained by the workmen.

docs.lead_paragraph: The steamship Alabama, G B. SCHENCK, commander, reached this port on Saturday. She made the voyage from Savannah in 58 hours. She brings papers to the 14th inst. The Republican has this item of news: SUDDEN DEATH.--JOSEPH GEORGE, Esq., one of the most respectable citizens of Savannah, died suddenly at his house yesterday morning, of apoplexy.
